Linux Screen allows you to:

Use multiple shell windows from a single SSH session.
Keep a shell active even through network disruptions.
Disconnect and re-connect to a shell sessions from multiple locations.
Run a long running process without maintaining an active shell session.

screen	   	   	   starter programmet
C+a			   generelle kontroll kommando, utføres før alle andre.
C+a ?			   screen help page
C+a c			   creates a new window
C+a n			   next screen window. Bruk p for previous
C+a d			   detach from screen. Keeps screen running. Start it up again with
C+a r			   reattach to screen.
C+a h			   creates a running log of the session
C+a W			   show all windows
C+a S			   create split screen
C+a TAB			   switch between split screens

C+a k			   Kill current window/session
exit			   exit screen session